    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - REASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="8">
            <title>MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the 4th-5th shift collar on the mainshaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c0">Figure 120</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022c0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022c0" filename="../figg13/g13022c0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 120. 4th - 5th Shift Collar</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 4th and 3rd speed gears into place (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c1">Figure 121</hotlnk>). Each gear has a shift collar bore which must face
                    the collar it will receive.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022c1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022c1" filename="../figg13/g13022c1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 121. 4th &#38; 3rd Speed Gears</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the 2nd-3rd shift collar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c2">Figure 122</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022c2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022c2" filename="../figg13/g13022c2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 122. 2nd - 3rd Shift Collar</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the mainshaft assembly spacer (ZTSE4287) onto the shift collar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c3">Figure 123</hotlnk>). Center the bolt with the fork bracket slot. This
                    tool holds the collar at the proper height for receiving the countershafts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022c3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022c3" filename="../figg13/g13022c3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 123. Mainshaft Assembly Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 2nd and 1st speed gears (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c4">Figure 124</hotlnk>). Visually center the gears on the shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022c4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022c4" filename="../figg13/g13022c4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 124. 2nd &#38; 1st Speed Gears</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 1st-reverse shift collar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c5">Figure 125</hotlnk>). Secure it with the snap ring.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022c5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022c5" filename="../figg13/g13022c5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 125. 1st - Reverse Shift Collar</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the countershafts together (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c6">Figure 126</hotlnk>). The blind splines are timing marks. Align them
                    across from one another.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022c6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022c6" filename="../figg13/g13022c6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 126. Align Timing Marks</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the gear shaft lifting fixture (ZTSE4288) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c7">Figure 127</hotlnk>). Now remove the mainshaft assembly spacer (ZTSE4287).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022c7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022c7" filename="../figg13/g13022c7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 127. Gear Shaft Lifting Fixture</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
